\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 124. G. demissum} Boiss., {\i Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov.}{\b  1}({\b 3}): 40 (1843) ({\i G. pedunculatum} Stoj. & Stefanov). Caespitose. Stems 3-8 cm, glabrous and smooth. Leaves (3-)5-6(-8) × (1-)1·3-2·5 mm, in whorls of (4-)5-6, flat, broadly oblanceolate, with short cartilaginous apex, smooth, scarcely decreasing in the inflorescence. Inflorescence very few-flowered; bracts leaf-like. Corolla 2·5-3 mm in diameter, yellowish-brown or greenish; lobes acute. Fruit smooth, glabrous. 2n = 22. {\i Snow-patches on calcareous soil. S. Bulgaria, N.E. Greece.} Bu Gr.
