\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 127. G. graecum} L., {\i Mantissa} 38 (1767). Perennial. Stems more or less woody at the base, with short basal internodes, usually erect, 4-angled, hairy. Leaves in whorls of 5-6, usually hairy. Inflorescence oblong; bracts 1·5-2 mm; pedicels 1-2 mm. Corolla c. 1·5 mm in diameter, purple-brownish-greenish; lobes acute. Fruit hairy.{\i  Dry crevices in calcareous rocks. Kriti.} Cr. (E. Aegean region and S.W. Anatolia.)
